<h1>React 19.2 &lt;Activity&gt; — Server Side Rendering + Hydration</h1>

<p>
  This page server-renders (<code>prerender: true</code>) and then hydrates the
  <code>ActivityTabSwitcher</code> component. Only the visible tab's content is
  included in the server HTML — React 19.2's server renderer skips
  <code>&lt;Activity mode="hidden"&gt;</code> subtrees, and the client renders them
  after hydration with no hydration mismatch.
  See <code>docs/oss/building-features/react-19-activity.md</code>.
</p>

<%= react_component("ActivityTabSwitcher",
  props: { initialTab: "profile" },
  prerender: true,
  id: "ActivityTabSwitcher-react-component-0") %>
